{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πᾰλιγ-γενεσία</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>rebirth, regeneration</b>, of the world, παλιγγενεσίας ἡγεμόνες, of Noah and his sons, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author = 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus] 2.144; ἡ ἀνάκτησις καὶ π. τῆς πατρίδος 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 11.3.9 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <b>renewal</b> of a race, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Corpus Hermeticum” 3.3 \">Refs</a>]; of persons, <b>beginning of a new life</b>, εἰς π. ὁρμᾶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.159, compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Musc.Enc.” 7 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: hence of <b>restoration</b> after exile, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Atticum” 6.6.4 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; <b>transmigration, reincarnation</b> of souls, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.998c\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; compare μετεμψύχωσις near the end <br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> in Stoic Philos., <b>rebirth</b> of the κόσμος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Chrysippus Stoicus 2.191: _plural_, [prev. work] 187, 2nd c.BC: Boethus Sidonius Stoicus 3.265; so later, ἡ περιοδικὴ π. τῶν ὅλων 2nd c.AD: Marcus Antoninus Imperator 11.1, compare 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus “in Platonis Timaeum commentarii” 3.241 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> in Medicine texts, <b>relapse</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 13.83\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>regrowth</b> of a tumour, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Antyllus Medicus cited in 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus 45.2.7. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in Roman Law, = <b>restitutio natalium</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Justinianus Imperator “Novellae” 18.11. \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in “NT.”, <br /><Level3><b>__III.1</b></Level3> <b>resurrection,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"NT.Matt.19.28. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>regeneration</b> by baptism, διὰ λουτροῦ παλιγγενεσίας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Tit.3.5. \">NT</a>]","strongNumber":"G3824","accentedUnicode":"παλιγγενεσία","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1074","matchingForm":"γενεά","stepTransliteration":"genea","gloss":"generation","_zh_tw_Gloss":"世代","_es_Gloss":"generación ","_zh_Gloss":"世代"},{"strongNumber":"G1075","matchingForm":"γενεαλογέω","stepTransliteration":"genealogeō","gloss":"to trace genealogy","_zh_tw_Gloss":"同譜","_es_Gloss":"contar la genealogía ","_zh_Gloss":"同谱"},{"strongNumber":"G1076","matchingForm":"γενεαλογία","stepTransliteration":"genealogia","gloss":"genealogy","_zh_tw_Gloss":"家譜","_es_Gloss":"genealogía ","_zh_Gloss":"家谱"},{"strongNumber":"G1078","matchingForm":"γένεσις","stepTransliteration":"genesis","gloss":"origin","_zh_tw_Gloss":"誕生, 起源","_es_Gloss":"origen ","_zh_Gloss":"诞生, 起源"},{"strongNumber":"G1085G","matchingForm":"γένος","stepTransliteration":"genos","gloss":"family: descendant","_zh_tw_Gloss":"族, 親族","_es_Gloss":"familia ","_zh_Gloss":"族, 亲族"},{"strongNumber":"G1085H","matchingForm":"γένος","stepTransliteration":"genos","gloss":"family: kind","_zh_tw_Gloss":"族, 親族","_es_Gloss":"familia ","_zh_Gloss":"族, 亲族"},{"strongNumber":"G3439","matchingForm":"μονογενής","stepTransliteration":"monogenēs","gloss":"unique","_zh_tw_Gloss":"獨生","_es_Gloss":"único","_zh_Gloss":"独生"},{"strongNumber":"G3825","matchingForm":"πάλιν","stepTransliteration":"palin","gloss":"again","_zh_tw_Gloss":"又","_es_Gloss":"otra vez","_zh_Gloss":"又"}],"shortDef":"renewal; rebirth, regeneration","mediumDef":"renewal; rebirth, regeneration <br /><b>a new birth; regeneration, renovation, renewal</b> <ref='Mat.19.28'>Mt. 19:28</ref>; <ref='Tit.3.5.'>Tit. 3:5.</ref> See unpublished Ph.D. dissertati